this command will show your Subscription
Get-AzSubscription


to select a particular subscribation
Set-Azcontext -Subscription f4281d5b-f223-4b90-87ca-af530b9758aa -Tenant {Tenant}
SubscriptionName     SubscriptionId                       Account   Environment
----------------     --------------                       -------   -----------
Azure subscription 1 f4281d5b-f223-4b90-87ca-af530b9758aa MSI@50342 AzureCloud


This Command will create resource group
PS /home/premkumar> New-AzResourceGroup -Name RG-22 -Location "Central India"                                                                                 
                         
ResourceGroupName : RG-22
Location          : centralindia
ProvisioningState : Succeeded
Tags              : 
ResourceId        : /subscriptions/f4281d5b-f223-4b90-87ca-af530b9758aa/resourceGroups/RG-22

this will delete resource group
Remove-AzResourceGroup -Name RG-22  

this will delete resource group forcefully
Remove-AzResourceGroup -Name RG-22 -Force
